      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but if the \"original meaning\" is sometimes ambiguous or hard to find, doesn't that just give judges more room to pick what they want and call it \"history\"? it feels like originalism can be used to justify ignoring modern standards of justice or equality just because they weren't around in the 1700s. doesn't that make it a pretty flawed way to run a modern society?",
